Package it.polimi.ingsw.messages.clientMessages.internal

  • Class Summary
    Class Description
    ChooseAction
    Class ChooseAction represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to ask the player to choose an action.
    DisplayMessage
    Class DisplayMessage represents a ViewMessage that instruct the CLI and the GUI to display a string message to the player.
    NewView
    Class NewView represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to display the view elements when a game starts or when the player is reconnecting.
    PrintChest
    Class PrintChest represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to show an updated chest.
    PrintDevDecks
    Class PrintDevDecks represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to show the updated development decks.
    PrintDevSpace
    Class PrintDevSpace represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to show an updated development space.
    PrintEndGame  
    PrintHandCards
    Class PrintHandCards represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to show the updated hand leader cards.
    PrintItinerary
    Class PrintItinerary represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to show an updated itinerary.
    PrintMarket
    Class PrintMarket represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to show the updated market.
    PrintPlayedCards
    Class PrintPlayedCards represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to show the played leader cards of a specified player.
    PrintWarehouse
    Class PrintWarehouse represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to show an updated warehouse.
    RequestPlayersNumber
    Class PrintChest represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to show the player the available lobbies he can join.
    SetupDiscard
    Class SetupDiscard represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to ask the player which initial leader cards he wants to discard.
    SetupResources
    Class SetupResources represents a ViewMessage that instructs the CLI and the GUI to ask the player where he wants to put his initial resources.
    ViewMessage
    Abstract class ViewMessage represents a message sent by the ClientView object, observed by both CLI and GUI, to instruct them on what is the next thing to do.
